The paper proposes a deep learning approach for collaborative filtering, which is a common task in machine learning and information retrieval. The use of distributional representation for users and items is a key aspect of the proposed framework, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques and the potential application to image and video recommendation systems suggest relevance to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
